                                </listBibl>
                            <note>As reported by Aḥmad Munzavī (in <foreign xml:lang="per">فهرست نسخه‌های خطی فارسی</foreign>) and Āqā Buzurg Tihrānī (in <foreign xml:lang="per">الذریعه</foreign>), only two copies of this work had already been seen:
                                one in the Library of Muḥammad ʿAlī Najafī in Najaf, and the other in Dār al-Kutub in Cairo. The copy of the Library of Ayatollah Ha'iri (Library of Faydiyya Seminary) in Qum was found after their report.</note>                            
